(num:1 text:Connect)
<b>supply Calliope mini with power</b><br>
Before you can start, the Calliope mini must be powered. There are two possibilities:
(pushdown:10)

<Grid><div>

(image: batterien_anschliessen.png)
(pushdown:40)

**External battery compartment**
1. fill the battery compartment with two batteries of type <b>AAA</b>. Make sure that the batteries are aligned correctly. 

2. take the battery block provided and carefully insert the small, <b>white plastic end (JST connector)</b> into the battery connector attached to the Calliope mini. 

Make sure that the closed end of the plug is at the top with the raised part in the middle. If the cable connector fits easily into the battery connector on the board, it is correct. 

</div><div>

(carousel…)
(image: computer_verbinden.jpg)
(image: computer_verbinden2.jpg)
(…carousel)

**computer**
1. take the USB cable and plug the smaller, narrower side into the USB port on the Calliope mini. This is located at the very top in the middle of the board.

2. plug the other end of the cable into the USB port on your computer.

</div></Grid>

